==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taro
<hw>Ta"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the Polynesian
name.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name for several aroid plants
(<spn>Colocasia antiquorum</spn>, var. <varn>esculenta</varn>,
<spn>Colocasia macrorhiza</spn>, etc.), and their rootstocks. They have
large ovate-sagittate leaves and large fleshy tuberous rootstocks, which
are cooked and used for food in tropical countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarot</ent>⟦br⟧
